<h1>Answers</h1>
			<br><div id = "ans-910"  class = "post">
				<h2>Answer</h2>
				<h3>Score ::3</h3>
				<p><p>There are a few potential reasons:</p>

<ul>
<li>You seem to have recently crossed over the threshold, so the badge simply hasn't been awarded yet. Some badges aren't awarded immediately, but instead with a batch script that's run daily.</li>
<li>You edit a lot of tag wikis. It's possible that the /users page tracks <em>all</em> edits, but the badge only counts edits to posts.</li>
<li>Maybe only edits to the <em>content</em> of a post are considered for the badge, and while you have 500 edits some are editing the tags of a question instead of the actual content of the post.</li>
</ul>

<p>These are just speculations, but I'll bet that at least one is true. Just keep editing, you'll get it eventually :)</p>
</p><br>
